<div class="box">
<p><span style="font-size:140%;"><span style="color: #2c4a78"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><strong>&quot;Comma&quot;</strong></span></span></span><br />
Personnel ID: <strong>43975095/280</strong></p>
<p>Real Name: <strong>Jaiden Sheridan Collins</strong><br />
Nationality: <strong>American</strong><br />
Sex: <strong>Female</strong><br />
Date of Birth: <strong>8/16/1996</strong></p>
<div class="page">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<div class="image-container floatright"><img src="http://firedawnfolder.wikidot.com/local--files/empty-spaces/jaiden.png" width="300 px" alt="jaiden.png" class="image" /></div>
<p><span style="font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do' ;">She's 27 today. Or, at least, according to the Coalition, when they confiscated her from her &quot;threat entity&quot; mother. I guess that's why birthdays never really struck a chord with her.</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do' ;">Her callsign was Comma, because she always had something to say — usually along the lines of &quot;sure, but why?&quot; Drove command up the wall, but, now that I think about it, I wonder why I didn't ask more questions myself.</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do' ;">I've finally got one now: where are you, Jai?</span></p>
</div>
<p><span style="font-size:125%;">Summary</span><br />
Missions-oriented, highly skilled special reconnaissance operative, proficient in stealth operations and improvisational combat. Extremely casual demeanor and particularly talkative, but intensely focused during operations and exceptionally loyal. Notably accelerated reaction time and excellent sensory awareness. Particularly close with team members <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">&quot;Medusa&quot;</span>, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">&quot;Lynx&quot;</span>, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">&quot;2N&quot;</span>, and &quot;Sparks&quot;.</p>
<div class="page">
<p><span style="font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do' ;">&quot;Close&quot; is exactly how I'd expect them to put it. It doesn't half describe it, but at the same time, I don't know how I'd put it, either. I mean, going through hell and back again really makes you cling to those you've got, even when they're long gone.</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do' ;">She watched Glenn die in her arms, but at least she was there for him until the very end. I'd never forgive myself if I couldn't do the same for her.</span></p>
</div>
